---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<section id="about" class="py-12 relative">
  <div
    class="max-w-6xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center"
  >
    <div class="relative group flex justify-center md:justify-end w-full">
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-tr from-cyan-500/10 to-blue-600/10 rounded-2xl blur-2xl opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition duration-1000"
      >
      </div>

      <div
        class="relative w-full max-w-sm rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border-8 border-slate-800/80 shadow-[0_20px_60px_-15px_rgba(0,0,0,0.8)] bg-[#1a1a1a] p-3"
        style="aspect-ratio: 828 / 1075;"
      >
        <div
          class="relative w-full h-full rounded-lg overflow-hidden border-2 border-white/5"
        >
          <img
            src="/profile.webp"
            alt="Carlos Pérez profile picture"
            width="828"
            height="1075"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover grayscale hover:grayscale-0 transition-all duration-500 scale-100 group-hover:scale-105"
            onerror="this.style.display='none'"
          />
          <div
            class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center text-slate-600 bg-[#121212] -z-10"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi:account" class="w-24 h-24 opacity-20" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2
        class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3"
      >
        <Icon name="mdi:account-outline" class="w-8 h-8 text-cyan-400" />
        About Me
      </h2>

      <div
        class="space-y-4 text-slate-400 text-base leading-relaxed text-pretty"
      >
        <p>
          Hello! I'm <strong class="text-cyan-400">Carlos Pérez</strong>, a
          Systems Engineering student in my 9th semester at UCC Montería. I
          specialize in Full Stack Development, focusing on <strong
            class="text-slate-200">Go and TypeScript</strong
          >—a stack I’ve mastered to build modern, high-performance, and
          type-safe architectures.
        </p>

        <p>
          My most significant technical challenge to date was developing
          <span class="text-slate-200">Sports Analytics</span>, where I handled
          complex API integrations for real-time data processing. This project
          allowed me to leverage <strong class="text-cyan-400"
            >Go’s native concurrency</strong
          > for a robust backend and TypeScript’s reliability for a seamless frontend,
          resulting in a truly scalable solution.
        </p>

        <p>
          When I’m not writing code, I’m analyzing <span class="text-slate-200"
            >e-sports strategies</span
          >
          in League of Legends, Valorant, and CS2. I approach gaming with the same
          analytical rigor I apply to software: identifying patterns, optimizing resources,
          and anticipating the next move. My goal is to bring this data-driven mindset
          to <strong class="text-cyan-400">high-growth startups</strong>
          where I can help scale impactful products.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-8 font-mono text-sm text-slate-300"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="mdi:map-marker" class="text-cyan-400 w-5 h-5" />
          Montería, Colombia
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="mdi:translate" class="text-cyan-400 w-5 h-5" />
          Spanish (Native)
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="mdi:school" class="text-cyan-400 w-5 h-5" />
          Systems Engineer (Student)
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="mdi:controller" class="text-cyan-400 w-5 h-5" />
          E-sports Strategy & Data Analytics
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
